.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20foreign%20ministry%3C%2Fa%3E%20spokesperson%20said%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20is%20taking%20the%20same%20brinkmanship%20approach%20to%20China%2C%20said%20Alex%20Capri%2C%20an%20international%20trade%20specialist%20and%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore's%20business%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20will%20take%20the%20same%20approach%20to%20China%20and%20I%20think%20Beijing%20will%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20welcome%20this%20transactional%20way%20of%20doing%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Capri%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-canada-mexico-trade-tariff-pauses-china-retaliation-border-fentanyl-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738661464000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a1de1ceb4be2fff9a362eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-canada-mexico-trade-tariff-pauses-china-retaliation-border-fentanyl-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20slapped%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20Canadian%20and%20Mexican%20imports%20to%20pressure%20them%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20illegal%20immigration%20and%20fentanyl.%20They%20caved.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22katherineli%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20Li%2CHuileng%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A58%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-canada-mexico-trade-tariff-pauses-china-retaliation-border-fentanyl-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20guest%20lecture%20college%20students%20on%20key%20money%20concepts%20every%20young%20person%20should%20understand.%20Every%20year%2C%20the%20simplest%20way%20to%20build%20wealth%20catches%20them%20by%20surprise.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223337%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Old%20Chapel%20on%20Middlebury%20College%20campus%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d5dcdbfebcc4d029d728f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222503%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOld%20Chapel%20on%20Middlebury%20College%20campus.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Greim%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI've%20spent%20hours%20talking%20to%20college%20students%20about%20personal%20finance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20of%20them%20don't%20fully%20understand%20how%20compounding%20works%20and%2C%20importantly%2C%20how%20to%20benefit%20from%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20high%20schools%20in%20the%20US%20are%20requiring%20students%20to%20take%20a%20personal%20finance%20class%2C%20but%20we%20need%20to%20keep%20talking%20about%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20January%2C%20Middlebury%20College%20invites%20me%20to%20its%20campus%20to%20talk%20to%20a%20group%20of%20students%20about%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guest%20lecture%20ranges%20between%2090%20and%20120%20minutes%20in%20length%20and%20is%20titled%20%26quot%3BGood%20Financial%20Hygiene%20%E2%80%94%20Lessons%20in%20Personal%20Finance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20a%20financial%20advisor%2C%20nor%20do%20I%20pretend%20to%20be%2C%20but%20in%20my%20decadelong%20career%20reporting%20on%20money%20and%20asking%20wealthy%20people%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20wish%20you'd%20known%20about%20money%20in%20your%2020s%3F%26quot%3B%20I've%20learned%20some%20key%20lessons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20these%20lessons%20%E2%80%94%20pay%20yourself%20first%2C%20automate%20your%20savings%20and%20investments%2C%20etc%20%E2%80%94%20are%20surprisingly%20simple%20and%20don't%20require%20a%20finance%20degree%2C%20or%20even%20a%20degree%20at%20all%2C%20to%20understand%20and%20use%20to%20your%20advantage.%20Had%20I%20understood%20them%20earlier%20and%20started%20building%20smart%20money%20habits%20in%20my%20late%20teens%20and%20early%2020s%2C%20I'd%20be%20in%20a%20stronger%20financial%20position%20now%20at%2032.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20convey%20that%20to%20the%20students%3A%20%3Cem%3ETime%20is%20on%20your%20side.%20Don't%20wait.%20Start%20now!%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22035d8fef-3a44-4f44-bbd3-c09cc959d673%5C%22%3EA%20two-part%20lecture%3A%20The%20reason%20we%20save%20is%20to%20invest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crux%20of%20the%20lecture%20is%20that%20putting%20your%20money%20to%20work%20is%20a%20powerful%20way%20to%20grow%20your%20wealth%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20before%20we%20pull%20out%20the%20compound%20interest%20calculator%20and%20discuss%20investment%20strategies%2C%20we%20start%20with%20two%20prompts%3A%20%3Cem%3EHow%20do%20you%20feel%20about%20money%3F%20How%20do%20you%20want%20to%20feel%20about%20money%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ask%20them%20to%20pull%20out%20their%20notebooks%20and%20do%20two%20to%20three%20minutes%20of%20independent%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answers%20to%20the%20first%20prompt%20represent%20their%20starting%20point.%20Everyone%20has%20a%20different%20starting%20point%20%E2%80%94%20we%20all%20come%20from%20different%20financial%20backgrounds%20%E2%80%94%20but%20where%20they%20start%20from%20really%20isn't%20all%20that%20important.%20What%20matters%20is%20that%20they%20have%20some%20level%20of%20control%20over%20their%20trajectory%2C%20and%20they%20get%20from%20what%20they%20wrote%20down%20for%20prompt%20No.%201%20to%20what%20they%20wrote%20down%20for%20prompt%20No.%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20we%20get%20into%20two%20components%20of%20personal%20finance%20that%20can%20impact%20trajectory%3A%20Saving%20%E2%80%94%20how%20to%20keep%20a%20portion%20of%20your%20income%20%E2%80%94%20and%20investing%2C%20which%20is%20the%20key%20to%20building%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20acknowledge%20the%20importance%20of%20paying%20yourself%20first.%20When%20they%20ask%20how%20much%2C%20I%20point%20to%20the%2050%2F30%2F20%20rule%20of%20thumb%2C%20which%20suggests%20putting%2050%25%20of%20your%20income%20toward%20needs%2C%2030%25%20toward%20wants%2C%20and%2020%25%20toward%20savings.%20I%20emphasize%20that%20starting%20with%20a%20small%20savings%20rate%20of%20even%20just%201%25%20is%20better%20than%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20students%20are%20familiar%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20budgeting%2C%20even%20if%20they%20don't%20actively%20budget.%20I%20challenge%20them%20to%20think%20about%20budgeting%20not%20as%20restrictive%2C%20as%20it's%20often%20portrayed%2C%20but%20as%20liberating.%20If%20they%20successfully%20divvy%20up%20their%20paycheck%20according%20to%20the%2050%2F30%2F20%20rule%2C%20for%20example%2C%20they%20have%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20to%20spend%20on%20whatever%20fills%20their%20cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20two%20is%20all%20about%20growing%20your%20savings%20by%20putting%20it%20to%20work%2C%20taking%20advantage%20of%20compound%20interest%2C%20and%20understanding%20that%20time%20is%20on%20your%20side%20as%20a%20young%20investor.%20Every%20year%2C%20without%20fail%2C%20this%20is%20the%20moment%20when%20the%20energy%20in%20the%20room%20shifts.%20Ears%20perk.%20Hands%20shoot%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20when%20I'm%20reminded%20that%20young%20people%20are%20fascinated%20by%20the%20concept%20of%20investing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20data%20shows%20this%20generation%20is%20curious%20enough%20to%20take%20action%3A%20Gen%20Z%20started%20investing%20at%20a%20much%20earlier%20age%20on%20average%2C%2019%2C%20than%20baby%20boomers%20(35)%20and%20millennials%20(25)%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frpc.cfainstitute.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F-%2Fmedia%2Fdocuments%2Farticle%2Findustry-research%2FGen_Z_and_Investing.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20Schwab%20Modern%20Wealth%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20a%20handful%20of%20my%20students%20don't%20fully%20understand%20how%20compounding%20works%20or%20how%20it%20relates%20to%20an%20investment%20account.%20They're%20smart%20kids%