sts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20mud%20volcano%2C%20deep%20beneath%20the%20icy%20waters%20of%20the%20Barents%20Sea%2C%20is%20flourishing%20with%20marine%20life%2C%20scientists%20have%20confirmed.%20The%20Borealis%20Mud%20Volcano%2C%20400%20metres%20below%20the%20surface%2C%20continuously%20releases%20methane-rich%20fluids%2C%20creating%20a%20unique%20deep-sea%20ecosystem%20that%20researchers%20now%20believe%20serves%20as%20a%20sanctuary%20for%20vulnerable%20species.%20The%20Barents%20Sea%20is%20in%20the%20Arctic%20Ocean%2C%20north%20of%20Norway%20and%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Borealis%20Mud%20Volcano%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fdirect-window-into-earth-underwater-volcano-discovered-in-barents-sea-4081270%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscovered%20in%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20scientists%20from%20UiT%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Arctic%20University%20of%20Norway%20using%20a%20remotely%20operated%20vehicle%20(ROV)%20called%20Aurora.%20The%20ROV%20captured%20high-resolution%20footage%20and%20collected%20samples%2C%20showing%20the%20seafloor%20around%20the%20volcano%20covered%20with%20carbonate%20deposits.%20This%20suggests%20that%20methane%20has%20been%20seeping%20from%20the%20site%20for%20thousands%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20regular%20volcanoes%20that%20erupt%20with%20lava%2C%20mud%20volcanoes%20release%20mud%2C%20gases%2C%20and%20water%20from%20beneath%20the%20Earth's%20crust.%20The%20methane-rich%20environment%20at%20Borealis%20has%20created%20a%20unique%20ecosystem%20where%20marine%20life%20has%20adapted%20and%20is%20thriving.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20extreme%20environment%2C%20the%20Borealis%20Mud%20Volcano%20is%20teeming%20with%20life.%20ROV%20footage%20and%20samples%20revealed%20a%20variety%20of%20marine%20creatures%2C%20including%20anemones%2C%20tube-dwelling%20worms%20called%20serpulidae%2C%20sea%20slugs%20(nudibranchs)%2C%20and%20small%20hydroid%20colonies%20clinging%20to%20the%20volcano's%20crust.%20Sparse%20octocoral%20colonies%2C%20which%20usually%20thrive%20in%20deep-sea%20habitats%2C%20were%20also%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20carbonate%20formations%20around%20the%20volcano%20serve%20as%20both%20a%20habitat%20and%20a%20refuge%20from%20bottom%20trawling%2C%20offering%20feeding%20grounds%20for%20fish.%20Scientists%20recorded%20large%20schools%20of%20saithe%2C%20spotted%20wolffish%2C%20and%20various%20redfish%20species%2C%20including%20the%20endangered%20Atlantic%20redfish%2C%20which%20has%20been%20severely%20overfished%20and%20is%20currently%20protected%20under%20a%20fishing%20moratorium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20all%20findings%20were%20positive.%20Researchers%20also%20spotted%20abandoned%20fishing%20gear%20tangled%20around%20the%20jagged%20carbonate%20rocks%2C%20evidence%20of%20human%20activity%20encroaching%20on%20this%20fragile%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBorealis%20is%20an%20oasis%20where%20different%20species%20can%20thrive%20and%20flourish%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1071753%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20study%20lead%20author%3C%2Fa%3E%20Giuliana%20Panieri%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20UiT%20The%20Arctic%20University%20of%20Norway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20calling%20the%20Borealis%20Mud%20Volcano%20a%20%E2%80%9Cde%20facto%20sanctuary%E2%80%9D%20for%20endangered%20species%2C%20emphasising%20the%20need%20for%20conservation%20efforts.%20Preserving%20this%20unique%20ecosystem%2C%20they%20argue%2C%20is%20crucial%20for%20maintaining%20marine%20biodiversity%20and%20understanding%20how%20geology%2C%20geochemistry%2C%20and%20biology%20interact%20in%20deep-sea%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20has%20broader%20implications%20for%20oceanic%20research.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Arctic%20seabed%20plays%20an%20important%20role%20in%20oil%20and%20