d%2C%26quot%3B%20Coles%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20January.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20has%20to%20go%20through%20a%20filter%20of%3A%20Is%20this%20about%20power%3F%20Is%20it%20about%20people%3F%20Is%20it%20about%20politics%3F%20If%20it's%20not%20about%20that%2C%20we're%20not%20interested.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224898%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20headshot%20of%20Joanna%20Coles.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6792a9812fcded5e907486ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223265%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJoanna%20Coles%20became%20co-owner%20of%20The%20Daily%20Beast%20in%20April%202024%2C%20along%20with%20former%20ABC%20boss%20Ben%20Sherwood.%3Cp%3ERoy%20Rochlin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESherwood%2C%20who's%20based%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20flies%20into%20the%20New%20York%20office%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20in%20the%20coming%20year%2C%20he%20and%20Coles%20would%20invest%20in%20%26quot%3Bmore%20original%20content%2C%20audio%2C%20video%2C%20and%20technology%20and%20tools%20for%20a%20more%20engaging%20experience%20for%20our%20readers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20December%2017%20all-hands%20meeting%2C%20the%20Beast's%20director%20of%20product%20management%20announced%20that%20it%20was%20aiming%20to%20launch%20a%20new%20lifestyle%20vertical%20by%20the%20third%20quarter.%20Coles%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20will%20headline%20a%20new%20%26quot%3BBeast%20Power%20100%26quot%3B%20event%20series%20this%20year%20and%20next%20in%20partnership%20with%20a%20tech%20sponsor.%20During%20the%20all-hands%2C%20The%20Daily%20Beast's%20president%20and%20chief%20operating%20officer%2C%20Keith%20Bonnici%2C%20said%20the%20event%20was%20part%20of%20a%20plan%20to%20build%20%26quot%3Ba%20business%20around%20Joanna%2C%26quot%3B%20leveraging%20Coles'%20relationships%20and%20connections%20to%20grow%20the%20Beast%20brand.%20The%20event%20series%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bseven-figure%20deal%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonnici%20told%20staffers.%20%26quot%3BVery%20excited%20about%20that.%20Clearly%20I%20like%20money%2C%20if%20you%20haven't%20figured%20that%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20have%20taken%20over%2C%20the%20Beast%20is%20light%20on%20the%20hard-hitting%20journalism%20it%20was%20once%20known%20for%3B%20instead%2C%20the%20site%20features%20aggregation%20and%20opinion%20columns%20from%20Coles'%20famous%20acquaintances%2C%20including%20the%20%26quot%3BSabrina%20the%20Teenage%20Witch%26quot%3B%20creator%20Nell%20Scovell%20and%20the%20%26quot%3BLast%20Week%20Tonight%26quot%3B%20writer%20Jill%20Twiss.%20Coles%20said%20she%20and%20Sherwood%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bvery%20clear%26quot%3B%20about%20their%20desire%20to%20hire%20more%20investigative%20reporters%20and%20publish%20more%20original%20journalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20industry%20executives%20are%20sympathetic%20to%20the%20challenge%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20face%3A%20finding%20a%20viable%20business%20model%20for%20an%20outlet%20that's%20never%20been%20profitable%20and%20has%20seen%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F11%2F03%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fdaily-beast-joanna-coles-ben-sherwood.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecline%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20audience%20traffic%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years.%20%26quot%3BI%20often%20find%20writers%20have%20been%20kept%20in%20the%20dark%20or%20don't%20want%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20business%20is%20super%20shitty%20and%20hanging%20on%20by%20a%20thread%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20media%20executive%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20are%20skeptical%20that%20the%20pair%20will%20be%20able%20to%20solve%20the%20dilemma%20that%20plagues%20most%20media%20companies%3A%20how%20to%20publish%20quality%20journalism%20while%20also%20making%20money.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20you're%20dealing%20with%20two%20executives%26quot%3B%20who%20%26quot%3Bcome%20from%20the%20most%20traditional%20forms%20of%20media%20in%20existence%3A%20print%20magazines%20and%20broadcast%20television%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20industry%20executive%20who's%20worked%20in%20media%20for%20almost%2030%20years%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20skill%20set%20is%20completely%20inapplicable%20to%20what%20they're%20trying%20to%20do.%20It%20would%20be%20like%20taking%20someone%20managing%20US%20Steel%20and%20saying%2C%20'I'm%20putting%20you%20in%20charge%20of%20OpenAI.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIAC%20launched%20The%20Daily%20Beast%20in%202008%20with%20the%20former%20Vanity%20Fair%20editor%20in%20chief%20Tina%20Brown%20at%20the%20helm.%20Its%20goal%2C%20as%20Brown%20wrote%20years%20later%2C%20was%20to%20combine%20%26quot%3Btabloid%20raciness%20with%20sophisticated%20wit.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%20that%20she%20relished%20her%20role%20as%20%26quot%3BDen%20Duchess%20to%20a%20group%20of%20wildly%20talented%20millennials%20having%20late-night%20office%20romances%20and%20lots%20of%20PG-13%20entertainment.%26quot%3B%20The%20site%20itself%20reeked%20of%20urgency%2C%20with%20splashy%20headlines%20in%20dramatic%20black%20and%20red.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223404%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20IAC%20Building.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6792a9d710c98eace913b896%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225100%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Daily%20Beast's%20New%20York%20City%20office%20is%20in%20the%20IAC%20Building.%3Cp%3EVW%20Pics%2FVWPics%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Beast%20hit%20plenty%20of%20road%20bumps%2C%20including%20a%20short-lived%20merger%20with%20Newsweek%20that%20precipitated%20Brown's%202013%20departure.%20After%20her%20exit%2C%20editorial%20leadership%20passed%20to%20John%20Avlon%2C%20the%20CNN%20political%20commentator%2C%20then%20to%20Noah%20Shachtman%2C%20an%20editor%20of%20the%20publication%20Foreign%20Policy%20who%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20editor%20in%20chief%20of%20Rolling%20Stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20never%20made%20a%20profit%2C%20the%20Beast%20became%20known%20for%20punching%20above%20its%20weight.%20It%20attracted%20top%20talent%2C%20especially%20on%20the%20political%20desk%3A%20Spencer%20Ackerman%2C%20Sam%20Stein%2C%20and%20Olivia%20Nuzzi%2C%20who%20has%20since%20become%20Beast%20fodder%20herself.%20Brandy%20Zadrozny's%20reporting%20on%20Vice%20helped%20shape%20the%20narrative%20around%20the%20beleaguered%20outlet%2C%20and%20after%20political%20reporter%20Roger%20Sollenberger's%20Herschel%20Walker%20scoop%2C%20the%20politician%20lost%20the%20Senate%20race.%20Shachtman%2C%20who%20ran%20the%20Beast%20from%202018%20to%202021%2C%20said%20that%20at%20its%20best%2C%20the%20site%20holds%20powerful%20people%20to%20account.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20that's%20needed%2C%26quot%3B%20Shachtman%20told%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3Bespecially%20now%20when%20so%20many%20other%20outlets%20are%20hiding%20under%20the%20rug.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20arrived%20at%20the%20Beast%2C%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20expected%20to%20be%20met%20with%20excitement%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Times.%20But%20the%20staff%20was%20skeptical%20from%20the%20start.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20honeymoon%20period%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20staffer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20basically%20them%20laying%20out%20the%20argument%20that%20we%20weren't%20working%20hard%20enough%2C%20our%20leadership%20had%20done%20everything%20wrong%20monetarily%2C%20the%20reporters%20were%20lazy%2C%20the%20editors%20were%20stupid%2C%20and%20it%20was%20their%20way%20or%20the%20highway%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20former%20staffer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherwood%20said%20his%20and%20Coles'%20critique%20%26quot%3Bwas%20never%20personal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20very%20hard%20for%20employees%20to%20hear%20the%20truth%20that%20had%20never%20really%20been%20shared%20with%20them%20before%3A%20the%20Beast%20was%20on%20track%20to%20lose%20more%20than%20%2436%20million%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years.%20Traffic%20had%20plummeted%20double%20digits.%20Subscriptions%20were%20collapsing.%20The%20tech%20and%20website%20were%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherwood%20said.%20He%20and%20Coles%2C%20he%20added%2C%20were%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20turn%20things%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20times%2C%20things%20got%20tense%20between%20them%20and%20their%20inherited%20staffers.%20A%20few%20months%20into%20her%20tenure%2C%20Coles%20held%20an%20hourlong%2C%20expletive-laden%20meeting%20with%20the%20politics%20reporter%20Jake%20Lahut%2C%20who%20was%20on%20vacation%20when%20Trump%20was%20shot%20and%20didn't%20file%20a%20story.%20%26quot%3BI%20used%20to%20hire%20a%20car%20and%20drive%20in%20godforsaken%20places%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnot%20sleep%20for%2024%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20Coles%20told%20Lahut%2C%20who%20worked%20at%20BI%20from%202020%20to%202022.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20working%20in%20much%2C%20much%20nicer%20conditions.%26quot%3B%20Coles%20repeatedly%20questioned%20whether%20Lahut%20had%20what%20it%20took%20to%20be%20a%20journalist.%20A%20few%20days%20later%2C%20Lahut%20resigned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Baragona%2C%20a%20former%20Beast%20media%20reporter%2C%20said%20that%20in%20pitching%20staff%20on%20what%20this%20new%20Daily%20Beast%20should%20look%20like%2C%20Coles%20kept%20saying%20she%20wanted%20to%20go%20back%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmarter%20version%20of%20tabloid%20journalism%2C%20back%20to%20the%20Tina%20Brown%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'You%20want%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20late%20aughts%2C%20which%20didn't%20work%3F'%26quot%3B%20Baragona%20told%20BI%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood's%20first%20all-hands%20meeting%20on%20April%2015%2C%20Baragona%20asked%20how%20they%20knew%20their%20Daily%20Beast%20wouldn't%20end%20up%20like%20The%20Messenger%2C%20an%20online%20publication%20founded%20by%20The%20Hill's%20Jimmy%20Finkelstein.%20The%20site%20launched%20in%20May%202023%20with%20a%20%2450%20million%20investment%20and%20folded%20less%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20laying%20off%20300%20employees%20and%20earning%20a%20reputation%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F01%2F31%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fmessenger-closing-down.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETimes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20biggest%20busts%26quot%3B%20in%20online%20news.%20It's%20normal%20for%20a%20staff%20full%20of%20reporters%20to%20press%20their%20bosses%20during%20meetings%2C%20but%20Baragona%20said%20Sherwood%20seemed%20offended%20by%20the%20question.%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20a%20little%20bit%20fired%20up%20when%20we%20get%20included%20in%20the%20same%20sentence%26quot%3B%20as%20The%20Messenger%2C%20Sherwood%20responded%20at%20the%20all-hands.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20what%20we're%20looking%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20many%20of%20the%20more%20than%2020%20former%20and%20current%20staffers%20who%20talked%20to%20BI%2C%20Coles%20seemed%20like%20a%20holdover%20from%20the%20world%20of%20glossy%20magazines.%20In%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20first%20all-hands%20meeting%2C%20she%20was%20interrupted%20by%20her%20cellphone%20ringing.%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20it's%20Kara%20Swisher%2C%26quot%3B%20Coles%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20podcast%20host.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20call%20her%20back.%26quot%3B%20At%20another%20point%20during%20the%20meeting%2C%20she%20recalled%20the%20night%20of%20the%202016%20election%2C%20when%20a%20colleague's%20husband%20invited%20her%20to%20come%20sit%20in%20the%20NBC%20News%20control%20room.%20There%20were%20two%20other%20people%20there%2C%20she%20said%3A%20Lorne%20Michaels%20and%20Steven%20Spielberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20Coles%20asked%20Tracy%20Connor%2C%20then%20the%20editor%20in%20chief%2C%20to%20point%20her%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Breporter%20who%20covers%20frivolous%20things.%26quot%3B%20Connor%20replied%20that%20the%20Beast%20did%20not%20cover%20frivolous%20things%20but%20that%20Coles%20should%20describe%20the%20story%20she%20wanted%20and%20Connor%20would%20do%20her%20best%20to%20assign%20it.%20Coles%2C%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20wanted%20a%20journalist%20to%20investigate%20Gov.%20Kristi%20Noem's%20budget%20for%20hair%2C%20makeup%2C%20and%20manicures.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20Joanna%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20staffer%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe%20didn't%20mean%20to%20demean%20what%20we%20do.%20That's%20her%20tabloid%20Daily%20Mail%20sensibility.%26quot%3B%20But%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20the%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20staffer%20added%2C%20were%20about%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20%26quot%3Bseverely%20misreading%20who%20we%20were.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou'd%20think%20they%20would've%20come%20in%20and%20been%20like%2C%20oh%20goody%2C%20we've%20got%20the%20keys%20to%20this%20kingdom%20to%20start%20some%20real%20trouble.%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20editor%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20first%20thing%20Joanna%20does%20is%20a%20Lauren%20S%C3%A1nchez%20correspondent.%20You%20couldn't%20have%20shown%20less%20of%20an%20understanding%20of%20what%20The%20Daily%20Beast%20was%20than%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20two%20months%20of%20coming%20on%20board%2C%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20fired%20Connor%2C%20a%20low-key%20New%20York%20Daily%20News%20alum%20who'd%20earned%20reporters'%20respect%2C%20and%20replaced%20her%20with%20the%20former%20Daily%20Mail%20editor%20Hugh%20Dougherty.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20an%20absolute%20savant%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20Coles%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20he's%20got%20a%20sort%20of%20Scottish%20rigor.%20He's%20in%20the%20office%20at%208%2C%20and%20he%20rarely%20leaves%20before%208.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDougherty%20seemed%20like%20an%20awkward%20fit%20for%20the%20newsroom's%20culture.%20Early%20in%20his%20tenure%20as%20executive%20editor%2C%20he%20criticized%20a%20photo%20editor%20over%20an%20illustration%20he%20didn't%20like%2C%20calling%20them%20%26quot%3Bbrain-damaged%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20multiple%20people%20who%20heard%20about%20the%20incident%20contemporaneously.%20He%20also%20called%20The%20Daily%20Beast's%20union%20a%20%26quot%3Bplague%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bcancer%2C%26quot%3B%20two%20former%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hugh%20Dougherty%2C%20Joanna%20Coles%2C%20and%20David%20Gardner%20holding%20drinks%20at%20a%20party.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679297b7ae09223df2bb4946%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESherwood%20and%20Coles%20hired%20the%20tabloid%20veteran%20Hugh%20Dougherty%2C%20left%2C%20to%20be%20The%20Daily%20Beast's%20executive%20editor%20and%20David%20Gardner%2C%20right%2C%20to%20be%20its%20chief%20national%20correspondent.%3Cp%3ELeigh%20Vogel%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Uber%2C%20X%20and%20The%20Free%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20Dougherty%20was%20chatting%20with%20writers%20in%20a%20weekend%20Slack%20channel.%20One%20reporter%20mentioned%20recapping%20a%20Fox%20News%20interview%2C%20and%20Dougherty%20replied%20that%20he%20hadn't%20realized%20the%20interviewee%20was%20on%20with%20%26quot%3BGay%20Trowdy%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20seemingly%20poking%20fun%20at%20former%20Rep.%20Trey%20Gowdy%2C%20now%20a%20Fox%20host.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDougherty%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20these%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaffers%20felt%20like%20they%20were%20increasingly%20being%20asked%20to%20cross%20ethical%20lines.%20Coles%2C%20who%20is%20on%20the%20board%20of%20Snapchat%2C%20expressed%20interest%20in%20negative%20stories%20about%20TikTok%2C%20its%20rival%2C%20one%20former%20staffer%20said.%20Former%20employees%20described%20three%20instances%20in%20which%20they%20were%20encouraged%20to%20use%20Chris%20Vlasto%20%E2%80%94%20a%20pal%20of%20Sherwood's%20who%20worked%20at%20ABC%20News%20and%20was%20contracted%20by%20the%20Beast%20to%20do%20communications%20%E2%80%94%20as%20an%20anonymous%20source%20in%20a%20story%3B%20in%20two%20of%20these%20cases%2C%20the%20former%20employees%20said%20this%20directive%20came%20from%20Sherwood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVlasto%20told%20BI%20that%2C%20as%20a%20longtime%20employee%20of%20ABC%2C%20he'd%20offered%20to%20share%20contacts%20and%20phone%20numbers%20with%20reporters.%20He%20said%20he%20never%20volunteered%20himself%20to%20be%20quoted%20anonymously.%20Sherwood%20added%20that%20Vlasto%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20fantastic%20resource%20for%20any%20reporters%20seeking%20to%20be%20smarter%20about%20topics%20related%20to%20the%20television%20industry%20or%20ABC%20News.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20occasion%2C%20Coles%20herself%20could%20be%20loose%20with%20the%20facts.%20On%20MSNBC's%20%26quot%3BMorning%20Joe%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20she%20thought%20Trump%20was%20microdosing%2C%20leading%20the%20host%20Jonathan%20Lemire%20to%20clarify%20that%20there%20was%20no%20evidence%20that%20Trump%20was%20taking%20drugs.%20And%20on%20a%20September%20episode%20of%20Ari%20Melber's%20show%2C%20she%20said%20that%20people%20had%20already%20begun%20early%20voting%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20After%20the%20show%20wrapped%2C%20her%20co-panelist%2C%20Molly%20Jong-Fast%2C%20pulled%20Coles%20aside%20and%20explained%20that%20early%20voting%20wouldn't%20start%20until%20mid-October%2C%20someone%20familiar%20with%20the%20interaction%20said.%20They%20added%20that%20Jong-Fast%20warned%20Coles%20about%20being%20so%20egregiously%20wrong%20on%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(The%20spokesperson%20said%20Coles%20was%20clearly%20joking%20with%20regards%20to%20Trump%20microdosing%20and%20said%20it's%20%26quot%3Bridiculous%26quot%3B%20to%20say%20she's%20loose%20with%20facts%20given%20her%20distinguished%20career.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20reporters%20worried%20that%20Coles'%20bravado%20would%20hurt%20their%20credibility%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20mention%20their%20relationships%20with%20key%20sources.%20During%20an%20April%20visit%20to%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20bureau%2C%20Coles%20suggested%20that%20the%20Beast's%20Washington%20reporters%20write%20about%20the%20fattest%20members%20of%20Congress%20and%20which%20lawmakers%20were%20on%20Ozempic.%20And%20after%20Puck%20reported%20that%20the%20ABC%20News%20chief%20Kim%20Godwin%20said%20that%20Black%20people%20don't%20watch%20the%20news%2C%20Coles%20assigned%20reporters%20to%20%26quot%3Bcall%20every%20famous%20Black%20person%20in%20the%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20Robin%20Roberts%20and%20Don%20Lemon%2C%20to%20ask%20them%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20claim.%20The%20story%20didn't%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColes%20said%20that%20many%20of%20her%20story%20ideas%20were%20attempts%20to%20start%20conversations%20among%20staffers.%20%26quot%3BI%20come%20from%20a%20background%20where%20people%20argue%20about%20ideas%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20understanding%20what%20an%20idea%20is%20and%20how%20you%20pursue%20it%2C%20and%20not%20being%20afraid%20of%20saying%20things%20out%20loud%20and%20not%20being%20afraid%20of%20being%20judged.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Beast%20first%20came%20on%20the%20scene%2C%20digital%20media%20still%20seemed%20like%20a%20good%20financial%20bet%3B%20the%20same%20year%20it%20launched%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2008%2F12%2Fhuffington-post-deal-25-million-at-100-million-valuation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Huffington%20Post%20was%20valued%20at%20%24100%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Digital%20publishers%20could%20count%20on%20revenue%20from%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esocial%20media%20sites%20like%20Facebook%2C%20brand-name%20advertisers%2C%20and%20venture%20capitalists%20hoping%20to%20recreate%20the%20HuffPost%20magic.%20These%20days%2C%20that%20has%20all%20but%20disappeared.%20Meta%2C%20which%20once%20built%20tools%20that%20advantaged%20sites%20like%20BuzzFeed%2C%20has%20pivoted%20away%20from%20hard%20news%2C%20and%20Google's%20new%20emphasis%20on%20AI-generated%20answers%20threatens%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-answers-search-advertising-end-of-web-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupend%20the%20digital%20ad%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%20and%202023%2C%20Diller%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20buyer%20for%20the%20Beast%2C%20meeting%20with%20people%20like%20Janice%20Min%20of%20The%20Ankler%20and%20BI's%20founder%20Henry%20Blodget.%20While%20there%20was%20substantial%20interest%20from%20private%20equity%2C%20Diller%20preferred%20not%20to%20see%20the%20outlet%20stripped%20for%20parts.%20He%20wanted%20to%20give%20the%20site%20a%20fighting%20chance%2C%20said%20someone%20privy%20to%20conversations%20about%20its%20future.%20For%20Diller%2C%20that%20meant%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20a%20star%20at%20the%20helm%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20person%20said.%20(Diller%20declined%20to%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Barry%20Diller%20and%20Diane%20von%20Furstenberg.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6792aa742fcded5e907486ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBarry%20Diller%2C%20pictured%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20the%20fashion%20designer%20Diane%20von%20Furstenberg%2C%20wanted%20to%20find%20a%20buyer%20who%20would%20breathe%20new%20life%20into%20the%20Beast%2C%20people%20close%20to%20him%20said.%3Cp%3EMarleen%20Moise%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EColes%20and%20Sherwood%20seemed%20to%20have%20everything%20Diller%20was%20looking%20for.%20They'd%20had%20long%20careers%20and%20were%20well-known%20names%20in%20their%20respective%20fields.%20The%20Beast%20was%20a%20chance%20for%20them%20to%20get%20back%20into%20the%20newsmaking%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColes%20started%20as%20a%20newspaper%20reporter%20in%20London%20(one%20of%20her%20early%20scoops%20famously%20came%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoanna-coles-risks-she-took-to-get-ahead-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econfronting%20someone%20while%20they%20were%20on%20the%20toilet%3C%2Fa%3E)%20before%20moving%20to%20the%20States.%20She%20became%20the%20editor%20in%20chief%20of%20Cosmopolitan%20in%202012%2C%20back%20when%20magazines%20were%20flush%2C%20and%20then%20the%20chief%20content%20officer%20at%20Hearst%20four%20years%20later.%20With%20her%20frosty%20pixie%20cut%20and%20treadmill%20desk%2C%20she%20was%20a%20larger-than-life%20figure%20at%20Hearst%2C%20%26quot%3Bswanning%20around%20in%20full%20Gucci%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20one%20former%20Hearst%20editor%20put%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColes%20left%20Hearst%20in%202018%20after%20Troy%20Young%20was%20appointed%20president.%20She%20continued%20to%20executive%20produce%20%26quot%3BThe%20Bold%20Type%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fictional%20show%20about%20women's%20magazines%20based%20loosely%20on%20her%20time%20as%20an%20editor%20in%20chief%20%E2%80%94%20until%20its%20cancellation%20in%202021.%20She%20tried%20her%20hand%20at%20various%20other%20ventures%2C%20including%20Boudica%2C%20a%20content%20platform%20to%20connect%20women%20in%20corporate%20America.%20She%20collaborated%20with%20the%20Twitch%20streamer%20Valkyrae%20to%20launch%20RFLCT%2C%20a%20blue-light-blocking%20cream%20that%20was%20blasted%20as%20a%20scam%20because%20of%20its%20lack%20of%20scientific%20bona%20fides.%20(%26quot%3BI%20am%20confident%20that%20if%20a%20male%20gamer%20had%20come%20up%20with%20RFLCT%20he%20would%20have%20been%20roundly%20applauded%2C%26quot%3B%20Coles%20said%20in%20a%202021%20statement%20to%20The%20Washington%20Post%20defending%20the%20product.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Coles%20partnered%20with%20the%20New%20York%20Islanders%20co-owner%20Jon%20Ledecky%20to%20launch%20several%20special-purpose%20acquisition%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20investment%20vehicles%20popular%20with%20celebrities%20at%20the%20time.%20Four%20years%20later%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eone%20of%20the%20SPACs%20was%20charged%20with%20making%20misleading%20statements%20to%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20investors%20in%20the%20SPACs'%20parent%20company%20sued%20Coles%20and%20other%20board%20members%2C%20alleging%20a%20breach%20of%20their%20fiduciary%20duty.%20The%20SEC%20charges%20were%20settled%2C%20with%20the%20SPAC%20neither%20admitting%20nor%20denying%20the%20commission's%20findings%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20is%20still%20active.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherwood%2C%20an%20ambitious%20executive%20from%20a%20well-heeled%20Beverly%20Hills%20family%2C%20got%20his%20start%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BGood%20Morning%20America%26quot%3B%20producer%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fben-sherwood-replacing-anne-sweeney-as-disneyabc-tv-president-2014-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworked%20his%20way%20up%20to%20the%20top%20job%20at%20ABC%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20presided%20over%20a%20run%20of%20successes%20at%20ABC%2C%20including%20leading%20%26quot%3BGMA%26quot%3B%20to%20its%20first%20ratings%20victory%20over%20the%20%26quot%3BToday%26quot%3B%20show.%20There%20were%20people%2C%20a%20former%20colleague%20of%20Sherwood's%20at%20ABC%20said%2C%20who%20wondered%20if%20Sherwood%20%26quot%3Bcould%20be%20Bob%20Iger%20someday.%26quot%3B%20When%20ABC%20merged%20with%20Fox%2C%20Disney%20kept%20the%20Fox%20TV%20executives%20to%20run%20entertainment%20and%20Sherwood%20left%20the%20company.%20%26quot%3BUsually%20when%20you're%20replaced%20at%20that%20level%20you're%20still%20a%20player%2C%20you%20get%20a%20production%20deal%20and%20eventually%20move%20into%20another%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20second%20former%20colleague%20said.%20Instead%2C%20Sherwood%20said%2C%20he%20went%20the%20entrepreneurial%20route%20and%20spent%20the%20next%20three%20years%20building%20the%20sports%20tech%20company%20Mojo%2C%20which%20he%20sold%20in%202023%20for%20an%20undisclosed%20sum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColes%20and%20Sherwood%20had%20known%20each%20other%20for%20a%20few%20years%20and%20would%20often%20exchange%20links%20and%20thoughts%20on%20the%20day's%20news.%20They'd%20discussed%20some%20sort%20of%20journalism%20team-up%20and%20had%20even%20come%20up%20with%20a%20name%2C%20Scoop%2C%20but%20didn't%20get%20much%20further.%20They%20saw%20each%20other%20as%20kindred%20spirits%2C%20the%20latter%20of%20Sherwood's%20former%20colleagues%20said.%20Sherwood%2C%20the%20person%20added%2C%20thought%20of%20himself%20as%20%26quot%3Bthis%20savant%26quot%3B%20who%20could%20speak%20to%20middle-American%20women%2C%20much%20as%20Coles'%20Cosmo%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20one%20of%20IAC's%20bankers%2C%20Jason%20Rapp%2C%20who%20suggested%20that%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20speak%20to%20Diller%20together.%20In%20their%20meeting%2C%20they%20impressed%20Diller%20with%20their%20ideas%20about%20what%20the%20future%20of%20media%20looked%20like%20and%20how%20the%20Beast%20might%20fit%20into%20that%20equation.%20%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20something%20that%20curated%20a%20lot%20of%20news%20out%20there%20that%20wasn't%20about%20the%20end%20of%20democracy%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Coles%20told%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColes%20and%20Sherwood%20spoke%20Diller's%20language%20and%20existed%20within%20the%20billionaire's%20rarefied%20social%20orbit.%20Coles%20and%20Diller's%20wife%2C%20the%20fashion%20designer%20Diane%20von%20Furstenberg%2C%20often%20appeared%20at%20events%20and%20on%20panels%20together%20and%20were%20both%20cast%20on%20season%20two%20of%20%26quot%3BProject%20Runway%20All%20Stars.%26quot%3B%20And%20Diller%20had%20started%20his%20career%20at%20ABC%2C%20where%20Sherwood%20came%20up.%20One%20person%20who%20knows%20both%20Coles%20and%20Diller%20said%20it%20probably%20didn't%20hurt%20that%20Coles%20was%20a%20charismatic%20blond%20British%20magazine%20star%20much%20like%20his%20old%20partner%2C%20Brown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20trio%20agreed%20to%20partner%20on%20a%20joint%20venture%2C%20with%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20taking%20a%2049%25%20equity%20stake.%20Actually%20bringing%20their%20vision%20to%20life%20%26quot%3Bwas%20like%20the%20girls'%20trip%20made%20it%20out%20of%20the%20group%20chat%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Daily%20Beast%20reporter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20long%20before%20the%20leaks%20began.%20Articles%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnymag.com%2Fintelligencer%2Farticle%2Fjoanna-coles-daily-beast-takeover.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hollywoodreporter.com%2Fnews%2Fgeneral-news%2Fdaily-beast-new-dc-chief-martin-pengelly-quits-1235929870%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Hollywood%20Reporter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fstyle%2Fmedia%2F2024%2F06%2F27%2Fdaily-beast-turmoil-coles-sherwood%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20quoted%20disgruntled%20Beast%20staffers%20describing%20Coles'%20story%20ideas%20as%20scattershot.%20Sherwood%20swept%20in%20to%20play%20good%20cop%2C%20holding%20a%20follow-up%20meeting%20with%20the%20DC%20team%20on%20May%201%20in%20which%20he%20seemed%20to%20try%20to%20defend%20Coles.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20doing%20a%20180%3B%20we're%20not%20here%20to%20cover%20Donald%20Trump's%20farts%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20assured%20the%20politics%20team%2C%20saying%20that%20Coles'%20ideas%20hadn't%20been%20real%20assignments.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20Jimmy%20Finkelstein%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20and%20Coles%20weren't%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20make%20you%20guys%20write%2070%20articles%20a%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20began%20gearing%20up%20for%20layoffs.%20But%20The%20Daily%20Beast's%20union%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20negotiating%20a%20new%20contract%2C%20which%20meant%20the%20co-owners%20couldn't%20immediately%20make%20changes.%20Instead%2C%20the%20union%20proposed%20presenting%20the%20staff%20with%20voluntary%20buyouts.%20As%20things%20in%20the%20office%20grew%20tenser%2C%20more%20people%20decided%20to%20leave.%20By%20the%20time%20Connor's%20exit%20was%20announced%20in%20June%2C%2012%20people%20had%20applied%20for%20a%20buyout%3B%20a%20few%20days%20after%20Dougherty%20took%20over%2C%2013%20more%20people%20joined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20buyout%20negotiations%2C%20Coles%20contacted%20multiple%20people%20directly%20to%20ask%20them%20to%20stay%20on%2C%20offering%20them%20more%20money%20and%20better%20positions.%20Three%20employees%20eventually%20rescinded%20their%20requests.%20In%20the%20end%2C%2022%20members%20took%20a%20buyout%2C%20resulting%20in%20%241.9%20million%20total%20in%20cuts.%20Management%20also%20laid%20off%20eight%20nonunion%20employees.%20When%20the%20restructuring%20was%20through%2C%20the%20Beast%20was%20down%20to%2013%20unionized%20staffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222108%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ben%20Sherwood%20wearing%20a%20suit%20in%20front%20of%20greenery.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6792aa1310c98eace913b8a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20former%20ABC%20boss%20Ben%20Sherwood%20told%20the%20Beast's%20politics%20team%20in%20May%20that%20he%20and%20Coles%20weren't%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20make%20you%20guys%20write%2070%20articles%20a%20day.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAlberto%20E.%20Rodriguez%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Variety%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20downsized%2C%20they%20were%20eager%20to%20attract%20new%20talent.%20One%20reporter%20said%20the%20duo%20described%20themselves%20in%20the%20interview%20process%20as%20%26quot%3Bpirates%20on%20a%20pirate%20ship%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20going%20to%20storm%20the%20beaches%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20phrasing%20that%20seemed%20cribbed%20from%20Logan%20Roy's%20speech%20to%20the%20ATN%20staff%20on%20%26quot%3BSuccession.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20same%20reporter%20described%20Coles%20as%20saying%20she%20wanted%20to%20hire%20Brits%20because%20she%20thought%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bsmarter%20than%20Americans.%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EShe%20and%20Sherwood%20tapped%20Martin%20Pengelly%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Guardian%20journalist%20who'd%20recently%20broken%20a%20story%20about%20Kristi%20Noem%2C%20South%20Dakota's%20governor%2C%20killing%20her%20dog%20%E2%80%94%20to%20run%20the%20DC%20bureau.%20Pengelly%20expected%20to%20take%20charge%20of%20a%20competent%2C%20well-oiled%20newsroom%2C%20someone%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20situation%20said.%20Instead%2C%20he%20found%20himself%20short-staffed.%20Two%20of%20his%20congressional%20reporters%20had%20just%20left%2C%20and%20two%20more%20were%20on%20leave%2C%20giving%20him%20a%20team%20of%20one.%20But%20he%20was%20still%20under%20pressure%20from%20Sherwood%20and%20Coles%20to%20churn%20out%20stories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20straw%2C%20people%20said%2C%20was%20when%20Coles%20told%20Pengelly%20to%20use%20an%20online%20test%20to%20determine%20whether%20Joe%20Biden%20had%20Alzheimer's%20for%20an%20article.%20After%20five%20weeks%20at%20the%20Beast%2C%20he%20quit%20without%20another%20job%20lined%20up.%20(Coles%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20this%20specific%20assignment.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20be%20an%20independent%20news%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20it%20was%20very%20clear%20there%20was%20something%20wrong%20with%20the%20president.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20people%20said%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20struggled%20to%20make%20hires.%20Coles%20told%20Variety%20in%20September%20that%20they'd%20wanted%20to%20bring%20in%20%26quot%3Bbig%20voices%26quot%3B%20but%20discovered%20that%20%26quot%3Btheir%20price%20was%20too%20rich%20or%20they%20weren't%20going%20to%20move%20the%20needle%20in%20the%20way%20we%20thought.%26quot%3B%20They%20tried%20for%20months%20to%20get%20new%20names%20for%20the%20politics%20team%2C%20putting%20out%20feelers%20to%20well-known%20reporters%20including%20Nuzzi%2C%20MSNBC's%20Sam%20Stein%2C%20and%20the%20investigative%20journalist%20Michael%20Isikoff.%20One%20politics%20reporter%20they%20attempted%20to%20hire%2C%20Cameron%20Joseph%2C%20went%20to%20The%20Christian%20Science%20Monitor%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20December%20all-hands%2C%20Coles%20told%20staff%20that%20she'd%20had%20%26quot%3Ba%20ton%20of%20outreach%26quot%3B%20from%20people%20clamoring%20to%20join%20the%20Beast.%20In%20fact%2C%20just%20that%20morning%2C%20a%20woman%20had%20recognized%20her%20during%20a%20coffee%20meeting.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20you%3B%20you're%20Joanna%20Coles%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20recalled%20the%20woman%20saying.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20love%20to%20write%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20way%2C%20Sherwood%20and%20Coles%20have%20succeeded%20where%20no%20one%20else%20has%3A%20They've%20made%20the%20Beast%20financially%20successful.%20In%20November%2C%20Bonnici%2C%20the%20Beast's%20COO%2C%20told%20Adweek%20that%20revenue%20was%20expected%20to%20grow%20by%2030%25%20in%202025.%20Traffic%20is%20up%2C%20too.%20According%20to%20the%20Times%2C%20data%20from%20the%20media%20analytics%20firm%20Comscore%20showed%20that%20the%20Beast%20had%2021.3%20million%20visitors%20to%20its%20site%20in%20September%2C%20compared%20with%20a%2013.8%20million%20monthly%20average%20in%202023.%20Coles%20said%20the%20Beast%20had%20seen%20a%20bump%20in%20traffic%20starting%20with%20the%20June%20presidential%20debate%2C%20presumably%20from%20readers%20who%20want%20to%20know%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20the%20hell%20is%20going%20on%20in%20America.%26quot%3B%20The%20question%20is%20what%20happens%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaffers%20have%20continued%20to%20leave.%20In%20addition%20to%20Lahut%2C%20the%20Beast%20has%20lost%20the%20managing%20editor%20Noor%20Ibrahim%2C%20the%20breaking%20news%20editor%20Rachel%20Olding%2C%20and%20the%20breaking%20news%20writer%20AJ%20McDougall.%20In%20October%2C%20it%20lost%20Roger%20Sollenberger%2C%20and%20the%20following%20month%2C%20Mini%20Racker%2C%20one%20of%20the%20few%20remaining%20DC%20staffers%2C%20left%20too.%20The%20investigative%20reporter%20Kate%20Briquelet%20departed%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColes%20and%20Sherwood%20are%20exploring%20new%20ways%20to%20make%20money.%20In%20addition%20to%20their%20new%20lifestyle%20vertical%20and%20event%20series%2C%20Coles%20told%20one%20reporter%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bvery%20good%20at%20spinning%20this%20stuff%20into%20TV%20and%20movies%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20she%20had%20plans%20to%20partner%20with%20Snapchat.%20The%20Daily%20Beast%20spokesperson%20said%20this%20partnership%20has%20yet%20to%20materialize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherwood%20said%20that%20even%20though%20he%20and%20Coles%20ended%202024%20with%20about%2031%25%20fewer%20employees%2C%20the%20Beast%20was%20publishing%20about%2070%20stories%20a%20day%20%E2%80%94%20an%20increase%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20added%2C%20from%20the%2040%20to%2050%20articles%20produced%20before%20the%20buyouts%20and%20layoffs.%20Sherwood%20sometimes%20contributes%20to%20this%20count%20himself.%20Recent%20stories%20include%20a%20piece%20on%20the%20Menendez%20brothers'%20resentencing%2C%20as%20well%20as%20one%20titled%20%26quot%3BCute%2C%20Cuddly%20%26amp%3B%20Commie!%20D.C.%20Welcomes%202%20New%20Chinese%20Pandas%26quot%3B%20and%20another%20with%20the%20headline%20%26quot%3BMcDonald's%20Serves%20Up%20the%2014-Ounce%20'Big%20Arch%2C'%20Its%20Biggest%20Hamburger%20Ever.%26quot%3B%20(Sherwood%20said%20he%20used%20a%20senior%20executive%20source%20to%20land%20the%20McDonald's%20scoop.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20publications%20like%20Vice%20and%20The%20Messenger%20shutter%20and%20layoffs%20become%20cyclical%2C%20the%20media%20industry%20is%20struggling%20to%20find%20a%20sustainable%20path%20forward.%20Outlets%20such%20as%20Puck%20have%20managed%20it%20by%20focusing%20on%20a%20specific%20audience%20%E2%80%94%20the%20power%20players%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20Hollywood%2C%20Washington%2C%20and%20Wall%20Street%20%E2%80%94%20and%20by%20charging%20%24100%20or%20more%20for%20an%20annual%20subscription.%20The%20Daily%20Beast%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20seems%20to%20be%20focused%20on%20traffic%20%E2%80%94%20a%20model%20that%20seems%20increasingly%20unsustainable%20as%20advertisers%20spend%20less%20and%20less%20in%20return%20for%20clicks.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20a%20September%20all-hands%20meeting%2C%20Bonnici%20said%20the%20Beast%20would%20eventually%20need%20to%20put%20time%20and%20resources%20back%20into%20investigative%20journalism%20to%20be%20of%20value%20to%20its%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20IAC%20and%20Diller%2C%20making%20money%20is%20certainly%20good.%20Coles%20said%20that%20while%20she%20and%20Sherwood%20had%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20operational%20and%20editorial%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Diller%20had%20%26quot%3Bbeen%20nothing%20but%20150%25%20supportive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20December%20podcast%20appearance%2C%20Diller%20said%20Coles%20and%20Sherwood%20wanted%20to%20build%20the%20Beast%20%26quot%3Binto%20a%20real%20business%20with%20substantial%20profits.%26quot%3B%20He%20called%20their%20plan%20ambitious%20but%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BSo%20far%2C%20they've%20gone%20faster%20to%20get%20it%20on%20even%20footing%20than%20I%20ever%20thought%20would%20be%20possible.%20So%20we'll%20see.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20people%20said%20Diller%20had%20held%20on%20to%20the%20site%20for%20so%20long%20because%20he%20cared%20about%20its%20role%20as%20a%20meaningful%20news%20source.%20%26quot%3BHe%20wants%20to%20do%20things%20that%20give%20him%20pride%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20things%20people%20in%20his%20peer%20group%20would%20read%20and%20talk%20about%20and%20respect%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20familiar%20with%20Diller's%20thinking%20said.%20The%20person%20questioned%20whether%20Diller%20is%20achieving%20that%20with%20this%20iteration%20of%20the%20Beast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20though%2C%20Sherwood%20and%20Coles%20are%20getting%20another%20shot%20at%20media%20relevance.%20So%20far%2C%20they've%20presented%20a%20united%20front.%20But%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20Ben%20is%20more%20worried%20than%20Joanna%26quot%3B%20about%20reputational%20damage%2C%20a%20reporter%20said.%20%26quot%3BJoanna%20is%20more%20like%3A%20'Fine%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20ride%20with%20us%3F%20I%20don't%20need%20you.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaily-beast-joanna-coles-ben-sherwood-barry-diller-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738659661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67913d582fcded5e90744760%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaily-beast-joanna-coles-ben-sherwood-barry-diller-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Daily%20Beast%20is%20profitable%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20Has%20it%20lost%20its%20bite%20to%20get%20there%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Claire%20Landsbaum%2CAnna%20Silman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaily-beast-joanna-coles-ben-sherwood-barry-diller-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Not%20a%20very%20big%20incident'%3A%20BJP%20MP%20Hema%20Malini%20on%20Maha%20Kumbh%20stampede%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738659602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117910164%2Cimgsize-1544580.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fnot-a-very-big-incident-bjp-mp-hema-malini-on-maha-kumbh-sta