%2Farticleshow%2F117909969.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20What%20Dangers%20Does%20India%20Face%20From%20A%20China-Pak-Bangladesh%20Tango%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETurbulence%20in%20Bangladesh%20now%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20rule%20rather%20than%20the%20exception.%20Protests%20by%20multiple%20groups%20are%20now%20almost%20a%20daily%20issue%2C%20including%20not%20just%20students%20of%20various%20universities%20but%20also%20madrassa%20teachers%20and%20the%20general%20public.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98students'%20of%20the%20Anti-Discrimination%20Movement%20are%20criticising%20the%20interim%20government%2C%20indicating%20that%20Chief%20Advisor%20Muhammad%20Yunus%20and%20his%20men%20may%20be%20increasingly%20isolated%20even%20as%20they%20use%20every%20reason%20in%20the%20book%20to%20delay%20elections.%20As%20Yunus%20and%20party%20try%20to%20overturn%20all%20the%20policies%20of%20Sheikh%20Hasina%2C%20particularly%20with%20regards%20to%20India%2C%20the%20question%20that%20has%20to%20be%20asked%20is%20whether%20a%20direction%20taken%20by%20an%20unelected%20government%20can%20be%20sustainable%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPakistan%20Wades%20In%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEntirely%20unexpectedly%2C%20Pakistan%20has%20chosen%20to%20wade%20into%20this%20chaos%2C%20fishing%20in%20troubled%20waters%20for%20possible%20gains.%20Immediately%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Hasina%20government%2C%20Syed%20Ahmed%20Maroof%2C%20the%20High%20Commissioner%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20met%20Yunus%20and%20held%20meetings%20with%20officials%2C%20including%20fisheries%20advisor%20Farida%20Akhter%2C%20education%20advisor%20Bidhan%20Chandra%20Roy%2C%20finance%20advisor%20Salehuddin%20Ahmed%2C%20and%20advisor%20on%20religious%20affairs%2C%20AFM%20Khalid%20Hossin%2C%20with%20the%20envoy%20calling%20for%20the%20restoration%20of%20direct%20flights%20and%20meeting%20a%20team%20from%20US-Bangla%20Airlines%20for%20the%20purpose.%20That%20started%20almost%20immediately%20when%20a%20Panama-flagged%20vessel%2C%20%3Cem%3EMV%20Yuan%20Xian%20Fa%20Zhan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20operated%20by%20a%20Chinese%20shipping%20company%2C%20docked%20in%20Chattogram%20in%20November%2C%20bringing%20goods%20like%20ceramic%20and%20raw%20material%20from%20Pakistan%20to%20Bangladesh.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20direct%20cargo%20movement%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%20A%20second%20consignment%20followed%20in%20December%2C%20with%20the%20Bangladeshi%20authorities%20removing%20a%20clause%20that%20requires%20physical%20inspection%20of%20any%20cargo%20arriving%20from%20Pakistan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Flurry%20Of%20Visits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bonhomie%20was%20also%20apparent%20at%20a%20December%20meeting%20in%20Cairo%20between%20Yunus%20and%20Sharif%2C%20where%20the%20former%20asked%20for%20a%20settlement%20of%20issues%20since%201971.%20This%20incidentally%20includes%20the%20repatriation%20of%20over%202%20lakh%20stranded%20Urdu-speaking%20people%20who%20were%20full%20Pakistani%20citizens%20before%20the%20Liberation.%20Prior%20to%20this%2C%20Yunus%20had%20invited%20Shahbaz%20for%20a%20meeting%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20General%20Assembly%20in%20September%20for%20a%20ceremony%20commemorating%20Bangladesh's%2050th%20year%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20United%20Nations.%20It%20had%20key%20Pakistani%20officials%20in%20attendance%2C%20including%20Defence%20Minister%20Khawaja%20Muhammad%20Asif%2C%20Information%20Minister%20Attaullah%20Tarar%2C%20and%20Special%20Assistant%20Tariq%20Fatemi.%20Further%20acts%20of%20%E2%80%98friendship'%20included%20removing%20security%20checks%20on%20incoming%20Pakistanis%2C%20which%20was%20done%20through%20the%20Home%20Ministry%2C%20overseen%20by%20known%20India-baiter%20Lt.%20Gen.%20(Retd.)%20Md.%20Jahangir%20Alam%20Chowdhury%2C%20under%20whose%20tenure%20there%20had%20been%20much%20bad%20blood%20on%20border%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistani%20High%20Commissioner%20has%20also%20remained%20extremely%20active%2C%20inviting%20the%20Bangladesh%20army%20to%20pay%20a%20visit%E2%80%94which%20they%20did%2C%20through%20a%20delegation%20led%20by%20Lieutenant%20General%20SM%20Kamrul%20Hassan%20(Principal%20Staff%20Officer).%20That%20Bangladesh%20did%20not%20send%20a%20high-level%20officer%20might%20showcase%20its%20caution%20in%20this%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERawalpindi%20remained%20unfazed.%20It%20sent%20to%20Dhaka%20a%20team%20led%20by%20Major%20General%20Shahid%20Amir%20Afsar%2C%20the%20ISI's%20Director-General%20of%20Analysis%20and%20earlier%20Pakistan's%20defence%20attache%20in%20Beijing.%20Incidentally%2C%20he%20is%20said%20to%20speak%20fluent%20Chinese.%20Foreign%20Minister%20Ishaq%20Dar%20is%20expected%20to%20visit%20Bangladesh%20soon%2C%20even%20as%20a%20Joint%20Business%20Council%20has%20been%20set%20up%20this%20January.%20The%20next%20move%20could%20be%20the%20actual%20supply%20of%20defence%20equipment%2C%20offered%20to%20Bangladesh%2C%20especially%20the%20JF-17%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20already%20announced%20training%20programme%20for%20Bangladeshi%20army%20senior%20officers.%20It's%20all%20moving%20very%20fast%2C%20despite%20political%20chaos%20within%20Pakistan%20and%20terrorist%20attacks%20almost%20daily.%20This%20is%20Rawalpindi%20exploiting%20its%20opportunity%20to%20the%20full%20before%20an%20elected%20government%20comes%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%20Takes%20a%20Bow%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Bangladesh%20Foreign%20Minister%20Touhid%20Hossain%20was%20on%20a%20rather%20anxious%20visit%20to%20Beijing%2C%20hoping%20that%20China%20would%20assist%20his%20country%20against%20a%20severe%20economic%20crisis%20that%20has%20pushed%20inflation%20to%20almost%2010%25.%20Hussain%20was%20apparently%20hoping%20that%20China%20would%20reduce%20interest%20rate%20on%20loans%20from%202-3%25%20to%201%25%2C%20and%20requested%20Beijing%20to%20extend%20the%20loan%20repayment%20period%20from%2020%20to%2030%20years.%20In%20the%20event%2C%20China%20tickboxed%20almost%20all%20requests.%20It%20agreed%20'in%20principle'%20to%20reduce%20interest%20rates%2C%20extended%20the%20repayment%20period%2C%20and%20notably%20also%20offered%20hospitals%20in%20Kunming%20for%20medical%20treatment%2C%20and%20funding%20another%20one%20in%20Dhaka%20for%20specialised%20treatment.%20It%20is%20well-known%20that%20%E2%80%98medical%20tourism'%20from%20Bangladesh%20is%20one%20of%20the%20mainstays%20of%20the%20relationship%20with%20Delhi%2C%20accounting%20for%20some%2050-60%25%20of%20the%20total%20medical%20tourism%20in%20India.%20Luo%20Zhaohui%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20China%20International%20Development%20Cooperation%20Agency%2C%20responded%20positively%20to%20requests%20for%20more%20concessional%20loans%20and%20projects%2C%20such%20as%20the%20upgradation%20and%20modernisation%20of%20Mongla%20Port%20and%20the%20establishment%20of%20digital%20connectivity%20and%204G%20expansion.%20Some%20of%20these%20loans%20are%20promised%20to%20be%20turned%20into%20grants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Chinese%20textile%20companies%20are%20shifting%20their%20base%20to%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20thus%20the%20development%20of%20ports%2C%20including%20Chattogram%2C%20is%20vital%20to%20Beijing.%20Nothing%20was%20said%20about%20the%20Teesta%20River%20project%E2%80%94a%20contentious%20issue%20for%20India%E2%80%94but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20it%20will%20be%20abandoned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoney%20Matters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20visit%20provides%20good%20relief%20to%20Dhaka.%20Between%202019%20and%202024%2C%20Dhaka%20received%20nearly%20as%20much%20Chinese%20investment%20as%20Pakistan%E2%80%94a%20far%20larger%20country%E2%80%94through%20the%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20(BRI).%20According%20to%20the%20Chinese%20ambassador%2C%20Bangladesh%20has%20received%20some%20%244.5%20billion%20under%20this%20initiative%2C%20with%20another%20%2422.94%20billion%20in%20construction%20contracts%2C%20generating%20about%205.5%20lakh%20jobs%20in%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20visit%2C%20the%20Jamaat-e-Islami%20had%20also%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Chinese%20ambassador%20for%20help%20on%20the%20Rohingya%20issue%2C%20an%20admittedly%20difficult%20problem%20for%20the%20small%2C%20highly%20overpopulated%20country.%20Beijing's%20fleet%20visit%20to%20Chattogram%20in%20early%20October%2C%20though%20probably%20planned%20before%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Hasina%20government%2C%20has%20also%20sent%20a%20powerful%20message%20of%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20goodwill%20for%20China%20is%20evident%20in%20that%20nothing%20has%20been%20said%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20Beijing%20did%20support%20Hasina%20fully%E2%80%94probably%20more%20than%20India%20in%20hard%20terms%E2%80%94and%20is%20owed%20%24251%20million%20in%20interest%20yearly%2C%20in%20Bangladesh's%20overall%20debt%20that%20has%20crossed%20a%20%24100%20bn%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20years.%20Islamabad%20may%20not%20enjoy%20the%20same%20goodwill%2C%20but%20it%20has%20something%20else%3A%20a%20strong%20ground%20presence%20and%20a%20good%20intelligence%20network%20through%20religious%20parties.%20It%20is%20also%2C%20as%20seen%20above%2C%20already%20digging%20into%20different%20sectors%2C%20using%20the%20anti-India%20sentiment%20to%20the%20full.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThree%20To%20Tango%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20offer%20of%20the%20JF-17s%20and%20the%20already%20supplied%20Chinese%20submarines%2C%20there%20is%20an%20undeniable%20triangular%20link%20developing.%20The%20question%20is%20whether%20a%20new%20government%20will%20continue%20with%20these%20policies%2C%20especially%20regarding%20Pakistan.%20In%20this%20instance%2C%20India%20has%20to%20act%20quickly%2C%20particularly%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20Rohingya%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98delivery'%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20enormous%20goodwill.%20That%20could%20simply%20be%20a%20generous%20aid%20package%20and%20a%20diplomatic%20outreach%20to%20Myanmar%2C%20despite%20the%20inherent%20risks%20in%20relations%20with%20that%20country.%20Though%20the%20US%20has%20reacted%20negatively%20to%20the%20Yunus%20administration%E2%80%94especially%20given%20its%20ties%20with%20former%20President%20Clinton%E2%80%94it%20is%20not%20in%20India's%20interest%20to%20alienate%20Dhaka.%20And%2C%20in%20all%20practicality%2C%20neither%20is%20it%20good%20for%20Bangladesh.%20In%20time%2C%20there%20will%20arise%20a%20need%20to%20publicise%20this%20reality%2C%20especially%20in%20terms%20of%20economic%20benefits%20for%20Dhaka%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Yunus's%20disastrous%20policies%20are%20being%20seen%20for%20what%20they%20are.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20media%20also%20needs%20to%20restrain%20itself%20in%20condemning%20the%20students%20and%20their%20very%20real%20%E2%80%98revolution'%2C%20and%20must%20acknowledge%20the%20very%20real%20and%20severe%20corruption%20that%20was%20endemic%20to%20parts%20of%20the%20previous%20government.%20All%20of%20this%20and%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20before%20a%20new%20government%20is%20elected%2C%20which%20will%20decide%20whether%20Yunus's%20self-serving%20policies%20are%20at%20all%20good%20for%20a%20country%20that%20once%20was%20known%20as%20an%20economic%20miracle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Tara%20Kartha%20is%20a%20former%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Security%20Council%20Secretariat)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738659360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fgmv4fu08_china-pak-bangladesh_625x300_04_February_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fdangers-india-faces-from-a-china-pakistan-bangladesh-speed-dial-7631233%22%2C%